                  </persName>
            . The prisoner came to my shop on the 1st of September; I saw him go out - Pinder gave me information; I followed him thirty or forty yards till I met a Policeman, I then gave him in charge - the ribbon had been taken from him in the shop; nothing was found on him, neither money nor any thing.</p>
